SIMPLE: indulgent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indulgent
<hw>In*dul"gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indulgens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>indulgere</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>indulgent</ets>. See <er>Indulge</er>.]</ety> <def>Prone to
indulge; yielding to the wishes, humor, or appetites of those under
one's care; compliant; not opposing or restraining; tolerant; mild;
favorable; not severe; <as>as, an <ex>indulgent</ex> parent</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>indulgent</qex> censure of posterity.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The feeble old, <qex>indulgent</qex> of their ease.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indulgential</ent>⟦br⟧
